    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-09-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-09-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="895"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d895">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 891.001.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Persian Chargé</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berkeley, Cal.</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-09-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 23, 1910</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I have received following cable from my Government [translation]: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>On Thursday, the 17th of Ramazan (Sept. 22),” His Imperial Highness the
                            Regent passed away. Act in accord with your duty.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <list>
                            <item>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hussein Kuli.</hi>
                            </item>
                            <item>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Mirza Ali Kuli Khan.</hi>
                            </item>
                        </list>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
